If you've ever visited the root page of a confluence site and gotten an error, that error page's title is stashed in the browser address bar forever more. Confluence should add an index.html or index.jsp or even index.action (assuming we override the welcome pages list to allow this) that renders something (anything!) more user friendly. We could make this page an alias for dashboard.action if necessary, but whatever we chose it needs to render, and not simply return an HTTP redirect.

I know it happens in Firefox 3.6.x, but probably others as well.

